cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for natural language understanding using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a popular technique in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a meta network to generate input-aware filters, which involves learning and optimization (cs.LG). The proposed framework is adaptive, which suggests a level of intelligence and decision-making, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of CNNs for image processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper involves training and optimization of neural networks, which is a topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
